Many donâ€™t understand and quick to make a statement or snap judgement. But as someone with a psychology background and is studying to be a counselling therapist - it is very clear to me how attachment has affected all the people on this show. Specifically how their earliest experiences of attachment with their caregiver or parents or earliest romantic relationships have affected them and shaped them. They have patterns of behaviours as every human does that is a result and product of their upbringing, environment, trauma, wounding, and conditioning. However, it is our responsibility to become aware of this but many never get that chance or know what to recognize or what to become aware of in the first place. Many donâ€™t have access to mental health services which is messed up and totally wrong. However, this inevitably leads to these relationship dynamics that can potentially be chaotic, dysfunctional, emotionally unstable or draining, cause emotional turmoil and pain and wounding. We repeat the patterns of our childhood or earliest attachments. Books that can bring awareness are: Adults or Emotionally Immature Parents, Attached, Anxiously Attached, reading about attachment style and wounding, Internal Family Systems and books about trauma - especially childhood trauma and how it can is affect and shape us.

I am writing to you today as a passionate fan of the show Siren. I believe that this show has the potential to be an incredible addition to your platform, and I would love to see it given the chance to shine.

As you may know, Siren was previously on another network, but it was canceled after only three seasons. This was devastating news for fans like me who had grown to love the show and its unique storyline. However, despite the cancellation, Siren has continued to gain more viewers and fans. The show has a dedicated following, and I know that I am not alone in my love for it.

What makes Siren so special is its incredible balance of drama, action, and suspense. The storyline is unlike anything else on TV, and it keeps me on the edge of my seat every week. The characters are so well-developed, and I have become invested in their lives and stories. I know that there are so many other fans out there who feel the same way.

That's why I am writing to you today. I believe that Siren deserves a second chance, and I think that Netflix is the perfect platform to give it that chance. With your incredible reach and resources, I know that you could help take this show to the next level. I can only imagine how amazing it would be to see Siren on Netflix, with all the creative freedom and support that your platform provides.

So please, Netflix, consider picking up Siren. Give this incredible show the chance to shine that it deserves. I know that there are so many other fans out there who would be overjoyed to see it on your platform. Thank you for your time, and please know that your support would mean the world to us.
